args: Ten down, a whole lot to go.
And it'll be over in no time\nif you all work together!
So come on, everyone!\nLet's keep at it!
Well, someone's sure struttin'\naround in fine fettle today.
How could I not be with what\nwe're creating here?
It's a village for sylvans, humans, rokkans,\nand anyone else who wants to live there!
It's the village I've always wanted,\nand I'm makin' it with my own hands!
Yeah. Yeah, I guess ya are...
What's wrong, Ranzal? You look gloomy.
Look. I like the idea of yer village.\nI really do. It's...nice.
But I don't get how a place chock full'a\ndifferent folks is gonna be all rainbows\nand sparkles.
So you don't want us to build it?!
'Course I want ya to build it, ya dope!\nHell, we got so many refugees from the\nEmpire, we need every hut we can spare.
So yer definitely smart to start whippin'\nup new places what for folks to live.
And I want this idea of yers to work.
I just ain't sure how easy it's gonna be to\nget all them different races and cultures\nto...ya know. Get along.
Oh, I know it ain't gonna be easy.
I fear we share your concerns, friend.\nMost of us have little experiences with\nother races at all, much less as neighbors.
Agreed. But so long as Luca is here,\nI think it has a chance to work.
Well, hell. Now I just sound like a\nbitter old man yellin' at progress.
Ha ha! Their support just means I\nhave to try that much harder, I guess.
It's time to take the first step on the path\nto a world where no one needs to fight.
And this village is gonna be that step.
All right, onto the next one!\nCareful, now!
We've cleared plenty of land.\nI might be able to get a head start\non tilling the fields.
I hope so; we need to build up\nour stores before winter arrives.
All right, everyone, let's do this.
Well, I was out on patrol just now...
When I found an álfr tree in the woods!
An álfr tree?! But that means...
Exactly! This is an álfr FOREST!
Uh, Luca? You mind filling us in?
Álfr trees are super unique plants that\ngrow deep inside certain forests.
And they are VERY special to sylvans.
We call 'em guardian trees of the forest.\nThey're precious things that bless all\nsylvan woods.
Any forest that contains an álfr tree\nis known as an álfr forest, which means\nthe whole area gets special treatment.
Don't forget the part about how our\nancestors were born FROM an álfr tree!
It is but a pretty bit of mythology.\nHowever, there are many sylvans\nwho accept such stories as fact.
Exactly. And those same folks believe that\nwhen sylvans die, they become one of the\ntrees inside an álfr forest.
So to sum up, this tree is an especially\npowerful symbol for our people.
It sounds much like a human religion.
All sylvan kids know to stay away from\nálfr forests unless there's a good reason.
And yet, such forests are extremely rare.\nMost sylvans can go a lifetime without\never setting foot in one.
So of course we find one THERE.
I am confused, Luca. I was taught that\nfinding an álfr tree was good fortune.
But now that we know this is an álfr forest,\nwe can't cut down any more trees.
I guess...we could try to find\na new place to build it? Maybe?

Are ya serious? Ya spent forever lookin'
for that spot! Even had us check the soil
quality and do a buncha topogoog...
torpholog... We did all them tests!
We ain't gonna find another place before\nwinter sets in, that's for damn sure.
And that means folks are gonna starve.
Ya really think some old tree\nis worth all that pain?
Hell yes, I heard it. Can't believe all\nour hard work is gonna be for nothing\nbecause of some stupid tree!
It's the sylvans' magic tree—not ours.\nMaybe we just continue on without 'em.
But we need Luca—he's the glue holding\nall of us together.
Just because Luca's a sylvan doesn't\nmean he'll abandon us. ...Right?
Or we just eliminate the problem\naltogether. By the root, as it were.
If somebody was to go into the woods\nand cut that tree down...
